  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\nCurrently we can add pragma in Vyper file, for example:\r\n\r\n`# @version 0.1.0b13`\r\n\r\nIt means Vyper compiler version 0.2.0 will fail to compile this Vyper file. But this is too primitive. We need to add [semver](https://docs.npmjs.com/misc/semver) capability.  It needs to support >=, ^, <, ==, for example:\r\n\r\n`# @version ==0.1.0b13`\r\n\r\nThis pragma line means only Vyper compiler version 0.1.0b13 can compile this Vyper file successfully.\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nSolidity pragma supports semver capability.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\nSemver specification is here: https://docs.npmjs.com/misc/semver\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\n\r\nIt's safe.\r\n\r\n## Dependencies\r\n\r\n\r\n## References\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/python-semver/python-semver\r\nhttps://vyper.readthedocs.io/en/latest/structure-of-a-contract.html\r\nhttps://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/v0.6.8/layout-of-source-files.html\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
